0 FILE 01fd.dat
0 Technic Ribbed Hose 120LDU Long (open file for usage guide)
0 Name: 78.dat
0 Author: Fredrik Gl—ckner
0 !LDRAW_ORG Part UPDATE 2000-02
0 !LICENSE Not redistributable : see NonCAreadme.txt
0 !HELP If you have a Ribbed Technic Hose you want to model in LDraw, you may
0 !HELP want to start by counting the number of "notches" on it.  Each subpart
0 !HELP "79.DAT" and "80.DAT" is used to model one single notch, the former
0 !HELP one at the end and the latter an arbitrary one in the middle.  The
0 !HELP distance between each notch should be 6.2LDU, and each subpart has the
0 !HELP notch centered in the origin.  For the end segments "79.DAT", the
0 !HELP distance from the origin to the very end of the hose is 2.5LDU.  This
0 !HELP way, the example hose below has a total length of 116.6LDU: Each of
0 !HELP the 17 segments have a length of 6.2LDU, while the end segments have a
0 !HELP length of 3.1LDU+2.5LDU each.
0 !HELP Note that the actual length of each hose segment is slightly longer
0 !HELP than 6.2LDU.  This is chosen so that the segments overlap if used to
0 !HELP model a curved hose.
0 !HISTORY 2000-09-30 [PTadmin] Official Update 2000-02
0 !HISTORY 2007-12-30 [PTadmin] Header formatted for Contributor Agreement
0 !HISTORY 2008-07-01 [PTadmin] Official Update 2008-01
